>Mike,
>I just towed my 71 Westy from Az. to Calif on all 4 wheels. Yes you do run
>the risk of burning up the engine or tranny if the Bus is left in gear. I
>did a simple check to make sure I didn't leave mine in gear. I would lift
>the engine cover and have my son pull the bus a few feet forward and watch
>the pulley on the generator to see if it moved. If it did move the bus was
>still in gear and I'd take it out of gear and repeat the process. I have
>towed bugs and busses all over hell and back and never had a problem.
>   Richard Kimball makes a very stout Bus tow bar that will work on your 69
>bus. It hooks up just like a Bug tow bar around the front beam.
>Britt
>Hillcountry Water Treatment

